Good evening, and welcome to our daily roundup of the latest developments on the coronavirus pandemic in Australia.
Tracking app to be reviewed for privacy issuesA mobile coronavirus tracking app will be reviewed for privacy issues before it is released, the attorney general confirmed to Guardian Australia.
Victorian students told to stay homeVictoria’s chief health officer, Brett Sutton, has advised the state government to continue remote learning for term two.
“In terms of Australia, we see the World Health Organization playing an important role, particularly in our region, and that’s important to Australia,” he said.
“We need to move away from this mindset of thinking that the coronavirus is an older person’s virus,” he said.